patch available.

  - In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved: i2c: lpi2c: Avoid calling clk_get_rate
    during transfer Instead of repeatedly calling clk_get_rate for each transfer, lock the clock rate and
    cache the value. A deadlock has been observed while adding tlv320aic32x4 audio codec to the system. When
    this clock provider adds its clock, the clk mutex is locked already, it needs to access i2c, which in
    return needs the mutex for clk_get_rate as well. (CVE-2024-40965)

Note that Nessus relies on the presence of the package as reported by the vendor.");
